n - 1 < n and n - 2 ≥ 1, raising both sides to the positive exponent n−2 preserves the strict inequality.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"integer inequality\",\n        \"monotonicity of x ↦ x^્ક for positive exponents\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"n · (n - 1)^(n - 2) ≤ n · n^(n - 2) = n^(n - 1).\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The first inequality follows from the previous step after multiplying by positive n, and the equality is exponent arithmetic.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 5\",\n        \"multiplication preserves order\",\n        \"exponent laws\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"n! < n^(n - 1).\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Combining n! = n·(n−1)! with the strict inequality from the induction hypothesis and the comparison of powers gives n! < n·(n−1)^(n−2) < n^(n−1).\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"step 6\",\n        \"transitivity of inequality\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": null\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization.\n\n## Previous attempt (failed)\nYour last formalization:\n{\"theorem\":{\"variables\":[{\"name\":\"n\",\"sort\":\"Int\"}],\"hypotheses\":[\"3 <= n\"],\"goal\":\"Factorial(n) < n ** (n - 1)\"},\"functions\":[],\"lemmas\":[{\"name\":\"factorial_recursive\",\"english\":\"For every integer m >= 1, factorial satisfies m! = m * (m-1)!\",\"vars\":[{\"name\":\"m\",\"sort\":\"Int\"}],\"body\":\"Implies(m >= 1, Factorial(m) == m * Factorial(m - 1))\"},{\"name\":\"factorial_3\",\"english\":\"3! = 6.\",\"vars\":[{\"name\":\"m\",\"sort\":\"Int\"}],\"body\":\"Implies(m == 3, Factorial(m) == 6)\"},{\"name\":\"factorial_lower_bound_step\",\"english\":\"If n >= 4 and (n-1)! < (n-1)^(n-2), then n! < n * (n-1)^(n-2).\",\"vars\":[{\"name\":\"n\",\"sort\":\"Int\"}],\"body\":\"Implies(And(n >= 4, Factorial(n - 1) < (n - 1) ** (n - 2)), Factorial(n) < n * (n - 1) ** (n - 2))\"},{\"name\":\"power_monotone_fixed_exp\",\"english\":\"If 0 <= a < b and k >= 1, then a^