ng the prime divisors from step 3 gives 2 + 3 + 7 + 13 = 25.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"arithmetic\",\n        \"step 3\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"25\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization.\n\n## Previous attempt (failed)\nYour last formalization:\n{\"theorem\":{\"variables\":[{\"name\":\"a\",\"sort\":\"Int\"},{\"name\":\"d\",\"sort\":\"Int\"}],\"hypotheses\":[\"a == 1092\"],\"goal\":\"Sum == 25\"},\"functions\":[{\"name\":\"Sum\",\"args\":[\"Int\"],\"result\":\"Int\"}],\"lemmas\":[{\"name\":\"prime_divisors_1092_sum\",\"english\":\"The prime divisors of 1092 are exactly 2, 3, 7, and 13, so their sum is 25.\",\"vars\":[{\"name\":\"d\",\"sort\":\"Int\"}],\"body\":\"Implies(And(d > 0, 1092 % d == 0, d == 2), True)\"}],\"instantiations\":[{\"lemma\":\"prime_divisors_1092_sum\",\"terms\":{\"d\":\"2\"}}]}\n\nErrors:\n- compile error at stage 'goal': eval failed for 'Sum == 25': Z3 AST expected\n\nFix these issues and return the corrected JSON object only."
