 rewrite.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 1\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"No number of the form 1 + p + p^2 + p^3 lies in the interval [2010,2019].\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Testing the possible primes shows p = 11 gives 1+11+121+1331 = 1464, while p = 13 gives 1+13+169+2197 = 2380; since the expression is strictly increasing in p, it cannot fall between 2010 and 2019.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"monotonicity of polynomials on प्राकृतिक numbers\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"Among numbers of the form (p+1)(q+1) with distinct primes p,q, the only value in [2010,2019] is 2016.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Since 2010 through 2019 are all even except 2011, 2013, 2015, 2017, 2019, the factors p+1 and q+1 must be at least 2 and at least one is even. Checking factor pairs of 2016 in the range compatible with primes gives 2016 = 48·42 = (47+1)(41+1), corresponding to distinct primes 47 and 41. For the other integers 2010, 2011, ..., 2019, no factorization into two numbers each one more than a prime matches the required parity and primality constraints.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"finite checking of small integers\",\n        \"properties of prime numbers\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"2016 satisfies the defining property of membership in S.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Take m = 47·41. Then m has exactly four divisors, namely 1, 41, 47, and 47·41, and their sum is 1+41+47+47·41 = 2016. Also 2010 ≤ 2016 ≤ 2019, so the condition in h₀ holds for n = 2016.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"direct verification\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"For every n ∈ S, we have n = 2016.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By h₀, any n in S must lie between 2010 and 2019 and must be the sum of divisors of some m with exactly four divisors. Steps 4 and 5 show that the only such n in this interval is 2016, so every element of S equals 2016.\",\n 