to 14 modulo 30 can be written in the form 30k + 14.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"definition of modular arithmetic\",\n        \"step 3\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"14 ≤ x.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"From x = 30k + 14 and the fact that x % 10 is a remainder, x is nonnegative enough to force k ≥ 0 in this setting; therefore x is at least 14. More directly, among all integers congruent to 14 modulo 30, the smallest is 14.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"properties of residues\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"14 ≤ x\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
